Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @diced butternut squash{300%g} on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pop on the top shelf of your #oven{} and roast until golden and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @British streaky bacon{4}(widthways into 1cm wide strips) (use #scissors{} for this if you like - it's much easier!)

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Put a large #saucepan{} of @water{750%ml} on to boil. Add the @KNORR Vegetable Stock{1}, stir to dissolve. Heat a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium heat. Add the onion and bacon. Stir and cook until the onion is soft and the bacon browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the chilli and the garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more, then stir in the @Arborio rice{175%g}. Cook for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a ladleful of the stock and stir. Once the rice has absorbed the stock, add another ladleful and continue to stir. Continue adding stock and stirring regularly, until all the stock has been absorbed by the rice. This should take ~{20-25%minutes}.

The risotto is ready when the rice is 'al dente' - cooked through but has a bit of firmness left in the middle. Once ready, remove from the heat. Add the cooked butternut squash, the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated), three-quarters of the parsley and a knob of @?butter{}.

Halve the @lemon{1/2}, add a squeeze of lemon juice, taste and season accordingly. Serve the bacon and butternut squash risotto in #bowls{} with the remaining parsley sprinkled over the top. Buon appetito!